<subSubSection id="BE7DBB30CB5C17FDEFEB8A040F276F91" pageId="178" pageNumber="179" type="distinguishing features">
<paragraph id="AE8F5D446C528DB6EFFCB586F76EFA9B" pageId="178" pageNumber="179">Distinguishing features.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="511236BD1650EE2DC55BE4FDB7259278" pageId="178" pageNumber="179">
The hybrid 
<taxonomicName id="E0A75E11CCDADE8D2888D7432024BF37" authorityName="L. f., Suppl. Pl. 136. 1782 [&quot; 1781 &quot;]. (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1782" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus floridus" order="Solanales" pageId="178" pageNumber="179" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="floridus">
Convolvulus scoparius 
<normalizedToken id="C27F06EF22E2EF75E75B76E6A09C18E6" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
floridus
</taxonomicName>
has leaves that are 1.12-4.86 mm wide, so intermediate in width between the parents. The inflorescence is generally compound unlike the simple inflorescences of 
<taxonomicName id="D420893875039ABA4CDA233933B9F4F2" authorityName="L. f., Suppl. Pl. 135. 1782 [&quot; 1781 &quot;]. (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1782" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus scoparius" order="Solanales" pageId="178" pageNumber="179" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scoparius">
<emphasis id="0060617E24B537241021BDC954261B0A" italics="true" pageId="178" pageNumber="179">Convolvulus scoparius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but less branched than that of 
<taxonomicName id="795CD8A98A04BBAC77E10C0287CF3F4C" authorityName="L. f., Suppl. Pl. 136. 1782 [&quot; 1781 &quot;]. (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1782" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus floridus" order="Solanales" pageId="178" pageNumber="179" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="floridus">
<emphasis id="127F1D9C8B2AF29BAA4AB69373D3C0D5" italics="true" pageId="178" pageNumber="179">Convolvulus floridus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
